 class UniformizedStateHistory
          A class to represent a complete state history of a continuous-time Markov chain in the interval [0,T] simulated using the Uniformization Method

This work is supported by NSF grant 0856099

Minin VN and Suchard MA (2008) Counting labeled transitions in continous-time Markov models of evolution.
